# AI Engineering Rules

This file defines the strict rules that all AI assistants must follow when modifying this codebase.

## 1. Architectural Integrity
- Follow the feature-based folder structure.
- Do not create components in `src/components` unless they are truly shared base primitives (shadcn/ui) or global layout elements.
- Domain-specific components belong in `src/features/{feature-name}/components`.

## 2. Design System & Styling
- Never hardcode colors, spacing, typography, or breakpoints.
- Use Tailwind CSS v4 variables mapped to our design tokens.
- All UI components must compose `src/components/ui` primitives. DO NOT recreate `Button`, `Input`, `Dialog`, etc.
- Use `Inter Tight` font variables (`font-sans`).

## 3. Code Quality & Patterns
- Default to React Server Components. Use `"use client"` only when necessary (hooks, events, browser APIs).
- Maintain Single Responsibility Principle (SRP). Keep components under 300-500 lines.
- Write strict TypeScript. Do not use `any` or `@ts-ignore` without a descriptive comment.
- Validate inputs using Zod.

## 4. Performance & Accessibility
- Use `next/image` and `next/font`.
- Ensure keyboard navigability and ARIA compliance.
- Keep Client Components as leaf nodes to minimize JavaScript payload.

## 5. Collaboration
- Check `task.md` or `docs/` for ongoing context before proposing large changes.
- Explain "why" in comments, not "what".
- Ensure new code passes `pnpm lint` and `pnpm build`.
